Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @ginger{1%unit}. Use a #teaspoon{} to easily scrape away the peel.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @aubergine{1%unit} and then cut into roughly 1cm pieces.

Halve the @bell pepper{1%unit} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Meanwhile, add the @rice{150%grams}, @vegetable stock sachet{1} and 300ml cold @water{300%ml} (double for 4p) to a #medium pot{}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and cook the rice (covered) for ~{10%minutes}.

Remove the #pot{} from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Mix @flour{3%tbsp}(double for 4p) with a pinch of @salt{pinch} in a #bowl{}.

In another bowl, beat @egg{1%unit}(double for 4p).

To a third bowl, add @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, @sesame seeds{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Toss @diced Irish chicken breast{260%grams} in flour. Next, in egg, then in sesame breadcrumbs.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to vacuum packing we use to keep it fresh.

Arrange chicken in a single layer on a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle over @oil{1%tbsp}(double for 4p).

Bake on the top shelf of the oven until chicken is cooked through and crispy, ~{16-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Place a #pan{} over high heat with a glug of @oil{to taste}.

When hot, add the aubergine, bell pepper, ginger and garlic.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} and fry until soft, ~{8-12%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Add the @soy sauce{1%sachet} along with @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%ml}(double both for 4p).

Cover and simmer for another ~{3-5%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Arrange the aubergine, bell pepper and rice in #deep plates{}.

Top with the sesame coated chicken.